  <static seed="1616" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation290.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>a</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{q} = \frac{8}{a+4} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>a = 8q-4</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{q\mathopen{}\left(a+4\right)}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{q} \amp = \frac{8}{a+4}   \\
   \frac{1}{q} \cdot q(a+4) \amp = \frac{8}{a+4} \cdot q(a+4) \\
   a+4 \amp = 8q \\
   a \amp = 8q - 4
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
